title: Iran's Protesters Mark 'Bloody Friday' Deaths
description: Demonstrators in southeastern Iran clashed with security forces as they gathered to mourn the deaths of dozens of people during the antigovernment protests that have swept across the country, in one of the most serious challenges to the clerical establishment in decades.

title: U.S., India Pledge Closer Economic Ties
description: The two countries are seeking to work more closely together to counter China’s manufacturing dominance.

title: Biden Aims to Boost Alliances, Ease China Tensions on Asia Trip
description: At a G-20 summit in Indonesia, the president will meet with Chinese leader Xi Jinping and attempt to maintain a unified front with allies on the Ukraine war.

title: Biden to Announce Restrictions on Methane Emissions at COP27
description: The president is moving to tighten restrictions on emissions of methane, a potent greenhouse gas, and boost funding for developing countries to adapt to the effects of climate change and transition to cleaner technologies.

title: Canada Confronts Shortage of Children's Pain Relievers
description: As flu season begins and Canada’s hospitals struggle with a surge of pediatric respiratory viruses, children’s Tylenol and Advil are in short supply there.

title: Russia's Shrinking Budget Surplus Limits War Options
description: The war in Ukraine and the sanctions it triggered are depleting Moscow’s coffers, hurting President Vladimir Putin’s ability to support the economy and fund the military.

title: Ukrainian Forces Gain on Kherson as Russia Says It Has Completed Retreat
description: President Volodymyr Zelensky said his country’s troops have recaptured dozens of settlements in their push toward the only regional capital seized by Russia since February.

title: Israel's Netanyahu Set to Get Mandate to Form His Sixth Government
description: Benjamin Netanyahu moved closer to becoming prime minister again after Israeli President Isaac Herzog said he would hand him a mandate to form a coalition expected to be made up of right-wing, ultranationalist and religious parties.

title: China Eases Zero-Covid Rules as Economic Toll and Frustrations Mount
description: China eased pandemic controls, as the country’s leaders seek to lessen the pain of a stringent zero-Covid policy that has exacted a heavy economic toll and stoked rising public resentment.

title: U.K. Economy Shrank in Third Quarter, Sliding Toward Recession
description: High energy costs, rising interest rates and a labor shortage weighed on British output in the three months through September.
